izarre this position is. Do not worry about not understanding where the compensation was if we had taken. I would be standing in confusion right alongside you in that case.} (13. fxe5 dxc4 14. bxc4 Rb8 15. Bc3 Qg4 16. Qxg4 Bxg4 {⇆ is one of the computer lines. There is no straightforward way for White to develop the queenside, as [d2]-[d3] will be an extremely vulnerable target after any ...[Rd8].}) (13. Bxe5 d4 {tries to lock our bishop in the center. We must avoid the trap of ...[f7]-[f6] with} 14. f5 $1) *

