ve been good, but this is simply much better. We may move the rook over to [g3] or [h3] but this isn't the entire picture. The main point is that we want to prevent any hope for Black of achieving the sabotaging ...[c5]-[c4]. As long as our knight stays on [d2], this ...[c4] advance is impossible.} c6 13. e4 {[%cal Ge1e2,Ya1f1,Ra6a5,Ga2a4] We want to play [Qe2], [Raf1] or [Rae1], and then [e4]-[e5]. White's position is much better. Because we've guarded against ...[c5]-[c4], Black is at a loss for active ideas. If Black plays ...[a6]-[a5], we will respond with [a2]-[a4], freezing the a-pawns and preventing any ...[a5]-[a4xb3] ideas.} *

