uces the potential for a challenge to White's healthy structure with ...[c5]-[c4]. It is due to this structural idea that we will look to recapture on [f3] with the queen rather than the knight (if we have placed it on [d2]) so that our knight can keep guard over the [c4]-square via [d2].} 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Qxf3 Nd7 12. e4 $1 c6 13. Nd2 $16 {[%csl Yc4][%cal Ge4e5,Ga1e1,Yd5d4,Yd2c4] We have healthy pressure on Black's center. If Black's d-pawn budges, the [d2]-knight will swarm the [c4]-square. Meanwhile, we can improve with [Rae1] and consider ideas such as [e4]-[e5] to lock out Black's minor pieces. We might consider [c2]-[c4] to crunch even further on the center, but this would take away the potential for our knight to install itself on that square going forward so we should be hesitant to commit to it. White has a much more fun position and also an objectively much better one.} *

