{The fifth and rarest type of situation: if the knight is ever defended by another one on [e7], DO NOT TRADE. If you were to trade, the [e7]-benchwarmer would simply replace the [c6]-knight in perfect harmony. In this situation, the knight on [e7] is quite disharmonious with the rest of Black's setup and will likely block the dark-squared bishop. With the knight on [e7], the bishop on [b5] is useless and so, throughout this repertoire, when the knight is aimed at [e7] we do not even commit the bishop to [b5] to arrive in this situation. Regardless, if you do find yourself here simply leave the bishop on [b5], and if it gets harassed, retreat to [e2], when the position would remain balanced. Remember, [Bxc6] would give away a healthy half of the bishop pair and we do not want to do this without getting something tangible in return.} 1. Z0 *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Bird Opening"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
