[FEN "r2qr1k1/p4ppp/2pb1n2/2ppp3/5P2/1P1PPQ1P/PBPN2P1/R4RK1 w - - 0 1"]
[PlyCount "2"]
[GameId "2127765595554339"]

{We have reached a complicated situation where Black has just played ...[e5]. Should we play [f4]-[f5] and attempt to build a healthy phalanx??? Simply put: if they can advance ...[e5]-[e4], then the answer is a resounding NO!} 1. f5 $2 {All seems fine. We plan to play [e4] on our next move, we might think to ourselves... Nothing could go wrong it would seem.} (1. Rae1 {⇆ was better, holding the tension on the e-file.}) 1... e4 $15 {Black throws a monkey wrench in our plans and their pieces begin to look better and better. Black's bishop peeks through [e5] at some weak squares on the kingside and if we ever trade on [e4], we will simply be giving their knight or rook a great outpost on [e4].} *

