[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2127765595583013"]

{Here we have a situation vs. the classic [c7]/[c6]-pawn jubilee. Our knight has flexibility; it can either go to [d2] to help advance [e3]-[e4], or it can transfer to [a4] via [c3] to target the weakened [c5]-square. Both options work. Keep in mind that we do not want to sit our knight indefinitely on [c3] if the bishop has been fianchettoed to [b2], as this would block the [b2]-dragon from sniping the long diagonal!} 1. Nbd2 $1 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Ge3e4]} (1. Nc3 $5 {is also interesting, but it always depends on the weakness of [c5]. In this exact position, the computer does not like this too much, as Black's [f6]-knight is ready to parry our pressure on [c5] with ...[Nf6]-[d7].}) *

