[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2127765595591206"]

{When the chop on [c6] has not taken place, it all depends on our [c1]-bishop. If we've already made preparations to fianchetto it on [b2], then the knight will go to [d2] where it will support [e3]-[e4] or further transfer to [f3] and then [e5]. The only exception regarding this as far as I can tell are a few positions in which our king has not yet committed to the kingside (where it remains placed on [e1]) and for expediency's sake (since moving to [d2] would require us to move a d-pawn) , we move the knight to [c3] to quickly castle queenside. Even in those situations, the knight quickly reroutes to [g3] via [e2].} 1. Nd2 $1 {[%cal Ge3e4,Yd2f3] So there are essentially no positions where the [b1]-knight stays on [c3] indefinitely with the Bishop on [b2].} *

