{Here, the black pawn is not on [c5] yet, and moreover, if we attack the [d5]-pawn, Black's queen would have to waste time recapturing there and then retreat, giving us ample time to make the break work.} 1. c4 $1 c5 {Black could aim for a good structure this way, and if they had one more move to play ...[Nf6], they would be better. But here we can beckon their queen out too soon.} (1... Nf6 2. cxd5 Nxd5 {, if Black has time for ...[c5] here, they will be better. Luckily, we can flick in [d2]-[d4] just in time.} 3. d4 {∞ , we got [d4] in before ...[c5] and can aim to play a quick [e3]-[e4]. These bonkers positions are analyzed in the Unusual Birds chapter.}) 2. cxd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8 4. Bc4 {While we have the same weakness on [d3] as always, we have gotten a few free tempi, which means we can build a healthy position with [d2]-[d3] and [e3]-[e4].} *

