7 {Black has finally dealt with the long diagonal.} 14. d3 {[%cal Ge3e4,Yf4f5] White reorients for central expansion! Now [e3]-[e4] looms.} Ne7 15. e4 {[%cal Gf4f5] White's position holds enormous potential due to its flexibility. We can push the e- or f-pawn, or trade on [d5]. We also have the bishop pair so it is probably in our best interest to open the position with [f4]-[f5], which will force open lines for the [h3]-bishop.} *

