 the mayor twice with this one.} 6. Ne5 $1 Qd6 7. O-O e6 8. d3 Be7 $2 9. Qe2 {Despite appearances, Black is already lost. The bishop on [f5] combined with our pressure on [c6] turn out to encompass a losing set of circumstances in combination with a hidden tactic related to the queen's placement on [d6]...} O-O $2 {Black falls deeper into the abyss. Now we see the trick.} 10. Bxc6 $1 {We can push [e4] now without worrying about ...[Qc5]+, hitting our [Bb5].} bxc6 11. e4 Bg6 12. Nxg6 $1 {Making way for [e4]-[e5].} hxg6 13. e5 Qc5+ 14. Be3 d4 15. exf6 $1 {Hitting the [Be7]. If Black takes a piece, we'll take [e7] back. Otherwise, we can escape the fork with [Ne4].} *

