...[Nc6] with a classic setup where they have escaped the wrath of our [Bf1]-[b5]. We must not let them achieve this peacefully. If that happens, Black will not just be equal but will have a slight edge!} 6. Ne5 {Attacking [c6] and [g4]; both of these details will come to matter as you will see.} Nc6 {Black asks to see the manager.} 7. g4 $1 {I'm the manager!} Bg6 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Bg2 c4 {This push would keep things close to equal by trading off the c-pawn.} 10. O-O (10. dxc4 $6 Bb4 {and the bishops give Black great compensation.}) 10... cxd3 11. cxd3 $132 {[%cal Gd1e2,Ge3e4,Gg1h1,Gf4f5] Things are equal technically, but double-edged. Give me White any day of the week.} *

