% of games going for it.} 6. a3 {Will the bishop trade or not?} Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 {We are fine with the doubled c-pawns. They are not particularly vulnerable and the dark-squared bishop was Black's best asset.} O-O 8. Be2 c5 9. O-O Nc6 10. a4 $13 {[%cal Gc1a3,Yd1e1,Ye1g3,Yg3h4,Gh2h3,Gg2g4] Our bishops looked a bit ugly, but they are getting better by the second! We will move our bishop from [c1] to [a3]. We can then think of improving our position by transferring our queen to the kingside via [e1]-[g3] or [e1]-[h4]. An idea for pawn play could be to advance [h2]-[h3] and [g2]-[g4] to begin harassing the [f5]-bishop. Things are equal, and White has a good share of chances.} *

