. Kd1 {[%cal Gb2c3,Gd1c1,Gc1b2] White will likely round up the [e4]-pawn shortly. White can gradually fix the king with [Bc3] and [Kc1]-[b2]. If we manage to achieve proper mobilization, we can count on a chunky advantage due to our great bishop.} (14. Kd1 {A sample variation is} Bxf1 15. Rxf1 Nc6 16. Qxe4 Ne7 17. Kc1 {⇆ . The fight is just getting started.}) *

