1. f4 d5 {Black counters with the d-pawn, gaining good control over the central light squares.} 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 {In this chapter, we'll go over this French setup in which Black voluntarily locks in the [c8]-bishop. For positions in which Black adopts the [e6]-[d5] structure with the bishop already out, check the Delayed French Setup chapter. While this may seem silly, these positions are considered one of the best ways to respond to the Bird, since without their bishop out on [g4] or [f5] we can't gain time harassing it. This chapter was probably the hardest for me in the entire course. It took several sleepless nights to work out all the details, but I feel confident in the approach I found. Several of the positions in this line are 0s according to the computer but heavily double-edged, making for a strong fight with great chances for both players.} 4. b3 Bd6 {This is played 15% of the time. The bishop fights more directly against White's control over the [e5]-square, but this scheme seems slightly awkward. The black pawn will likely come to [c5] at some point and that formation is traditionally best paired with a bishop on [e7]. By blocking the d-file, it will be hard for Black to push for ...[d5]-[d4], which is a common idea in other lines.} 5. Bb2 O-O 6. Rg1 {[%cal Gg2g4,Gg4g5] This move is a rarity and the resulting position has only been reached 24 times. It will certainly take your opponent by surprise. Buckle up, it's gonna be a bumpy ride.} c5 {Preparing ...[d5]-[d4] to stunt White's pressure along the long diagonal.} 7. g4 d4 {Objectively the best move although to be fair, it has never been played so far in the few games to reach this position.} 8. Na3 {[%cal Ga3c4] Our knight heads to the compromised [c4]-square.} Nc6 9. Nc4 {[%csl Rd6] We'd love to trade on [d6] so Black is best advised to retreat.} Bc7 10. g5 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Gg5f6] Booting the knight as expected.} Nd7 11. Bd3 $132 {[%csl Gb2,Gd3][%cal Gb2g7,Gd3h7,Gd1e2,Ge1c1] Lining up on the kingside. The position is extremely chaotic though the computer assures me things are balanced. We will aim to play [Qe2] and castle queenside while keeping an eye out for enterprising bishop sacrifices.} *

