ly hold off on castling queenside, as the black pawns have already advanced far. The king might stay on [e1] or hop to [f2] depending on circumstances. We will always be on the lookout for making [g5]-[g6] work. Keep in mind that [h5]-[h6] will allow Black to close up the kingside with ...[g7]-[g6], making any attack almost impossible. This is why [g5]-[g6], which initiates tension against the two pawns, is better, as it guarantees the opening of certain files.} *

