s very simple and straightforward. Black will simply march up the queenside with the a-, b-, and c-pawns. The position objectively remains level but Black's game is easier.}) 9... a6 {Black would love to play ...[b7]-[b5] if possible.} 10. Nc3 {Controlling [b5].} Rb8 11. Qe2 {[%cal Gd2d3,Ge3e4] Keeping control over the queenside. We can consider [d2]-[d3] and [e3]-[e4] to expand in the center going forward. The game is balanced and its complicated nature will benefit the player who has more experience.} *

