rtant note is that ...[Rg8] will often be met by [Bxf6], attacking the black queen while removing the defender of the [g8]-rook.}) 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. Ng5 {[%csl Gb2,Gb5,Gg1,Gg5,Rh2] White is down 2 pawns but our compensation is enormous. Black's knight is trapped and White's pieces exert tremendous pressure on Black's kingside. The opponent has to walk a tightrope of only moves.} h5 $1 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Gh2g4] Paving the way for the knight's escape.} 10. Rh1 Ng4 $4 11. Qxg4 {A splendid queen sacrifice to claim a decisive advantage.} hxg4 12. Rxh8+ Bf8 13. Bxg7 {[%csl Re8,Rf8][%cal Gh8e8] White has already gotten a rook and a knight for our investment and we will soon reap the bishop on [f8] also. With good technique, White has every reason to expect victory.} *

