[d3] and [Nb1]-[d2]-[f3], which would be strong and simple. In general, this structure with pawns on [c6] and [c5] is unequivocally worse for Black if the light-squared bishop is still on the board. If it has managed to be traded, as we will see in the main lines, Black has every reason to fight for equality.} *

