ng in on the kingside but is simply too late; [Qh6] will come next and the computer insists it's forced checkmate in 11!} dxc2 20. Qh6 c1=Q+ 21. Bxc1 Rxc1+ 22. Kf2 Rfc8 (22... Bxf6 23. exf6 {and [Qg7] will end everything.}) 23. Qxh7+ Kf8 24. Qxf7# {I'd like to stress how thematic this turn of events was. Our pawn on [e5] combined with the closed nature of the center gave us a free hand on the kingside. Black had to fight the tide by opening the center as quickly as possible with ...[c5]-[c4]. Because Black waited too long, their pieces didn't have any time to bother ours before checkmate was delivered.} *

