 [c1] and then later [g5]. An important side note is that if Black plays ...[a5] to advance ...[a5]-[a4] and trade our pawn off, then we will want to respond with [a2]-[a4], freezing the pawn on [a5] where it will be potentially weak and a target for our bishop from [c3] or [d2].} *

