h Black's pieces terminally back and White will be able to win with play on the d-file and pressure on the weak pawn on [b7].} e5 {Black's only try to avert this positional disaster.} 17. f5 $18 {[%csl Rd5,Rd6][%cal Ga1d1,Yg2g4,Yg4g5,Yc3d5] The cure is worse than the disease. Black's bishop is permanently awful and the [d5]-square is weak. White has a simple plan of doubling on the d-file and advancing [g2]-[g4]-[g5], kicking the [f6]-knight out, and allowing the [c3]-knight to gain the high ground on [d5].} *

