1. f4 d5 {Black counters with the d-pawn, gaining good control over the central light squares.} 2. Nf3 c5 3. e3 Nf6 {This chapter will deal with Black's attempts to set up the French structure with ...[e6] with the [c8]-bishop already placed outside on [g4] or [f5]. This tends to be a bit too idealistic for Black and they often get into trouble with the quintessential broken queenside.} 4. b3 (4. b3 {If Black plays} e6 {, this will just transpose to the French Setup chapter.}) 4... Bg4 5. Bb2 e6 6. h3 {Snagging the bishop pair as usual.} Bh5 {Black attempts to keep the pressure.} 7. Bb5+ {Before we know whether or not to push [g2]-[g4] we want to see how Black will block the check.} Nbd7 {Despite how natural this appears, it is a losing mistake.} 8. g4 Bg6 9. g5 $18 {[%csl Rd7,Rf6][%cal Gg5f6,Gf3e5,Gb5e8] Booting the knight out. Once the knight moves, [Nf3]-[e5] will splash Black's [d7]-knight with a gallon of cold water.} *

