st better.} Nxe5 8. Nxd5 {[%csl Re7][%cal Gd5e7,Gd5c7] With a tempo against the black queen.} Qd6 9. Nxe5 Qxe5 10. Qd4 $1 {Simple and strong. The queen trade promises us a close to decisive advantage in the endgame due to the extra pawn. The [d5]-knight's pressure on [c7] is quite annoying and will be a recurring theme in the middlegame.} Bd6 11. Bd2 $16 {[%cal Ge1c1,Gd2c3] With castle queenside and [Bd2]-[c3] to follow, we have every reason to be optimistic.} *

