ead doesn't improve Black's quest for equality since after} 10. Bc4 Qd7 11. Bd2 {(to prevent any ...[Na5] business, finishing development is problematic. Black has to constantly watch out for [d5] and [h3] ideas, while we can just continue to improve our position with moves like [Rd1], [Nc3], [a4], etc.)}) 10. Nc3 Be6 11. e4 $16 {[%csl Rg8,Rh8][%cal Gb3e6] The pawn on [d5] continues to be a source of pain for Black. Keeping control of it and in the bigger picture managing to develop properly are two issues Black will have a sustained discomfort over.} *

