h our pawns gaining tempi for any pawn storm. So it makes no sense to avoid castling kingside now.} 12. O-O d4 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Gf3d2,Gd2c4] Black wants to give away [d4] and [c5] for our [e3]-pawn and our [f4]-pawn which will hang after [exd4]. We have a beautiful rejoinder to immediately aim at the weak [c4]-square with our knight.} 13. Nd2 $1 dxe3 14. Nc4 {[%csl Re3] e3's days are numbered. When we recapture, we will be able to claim a huge structural advantage in view of the weak black pawns and great [b2]-bishop.} Nd5 {[%csl Rf4] Targeting [f4] and casting doubt over White's idealistic plan of playing [Qe2] and scooping up the [e3]-apple.} 15. Qg4 $1 {[%csl Rg7][%cal Gg4g7] Big threats.} g6 16. Rae1 {[%csl Re3][%cal Gg1h1,Gc4e3] We don't want to take on [e3] just yet since Black has the clearance trick of ...[c5]-[c4] followed by a ...[Bc5] pin of our rook and king. So we will simply move our king out of the way to [h1] and then collect on [e3].} *

