h our pawns gaining tempi for any pawn storm. So it makes no sense to avoid castling kingside now.} 12. O-O c6 13. Ne5 Qc7 14. Qf3 $14 {A fine square for the queen. We have good control over [e5] and Black's position lacks flexibility and play. We will slowly play on the kingside with ideas like [Rae1] and [e3]-[e4]. One key point is that after [e3]-[e4], if Black trades with ...[dxe4], we will recapture with [dxe4], when Black's c-pawns have become isolated and particularly vulnerable. On the other hand, if Black responds to [e3]-[e4] with ...[d5]-[d4], we can transfer our knight from [e5] to the wonderful [c4]-outpost, and play for [c2]-[c3] to crunch against the [d4]-concrete blocking our bishop. White is slightly better, but the more important detail is that our position is so much easier to play.} *

