reat outposts on [e4] and [c4] and clear targets on [e5] and [c5].}) (14... f5 $1) 15. Nc4 {[%csl Ra5][%cal Ga6a5,Ga2a4,Gb2c1,Gc1d2] White is more comfortable here. We will slowly reroute the bishop away from pointing at concrete via [c1]-[d2] where it will be placed optimally for whatever follows. We can consider [f4]-[f5] or [e4]-[e5] depending on what course the game takes. While the computer insists things are close to equal, I don't think anyone would prefer to take Black here. Another point is that whenever Black plays ...[a6]-[a5], we will play [a2]-[a4], fixing the pawn as a permanent target on the exposed [a5]-square.} *

