 it as it would challenge the strong knight on [f5] and force an interesting exchange of our [e3]-pawn for their [d5]-pawn.} b6 11. e4 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Rb8 14. g4 {This is some extra spicy chess here.} Nd4 15. Nxd4 cxd4 16. Bxd4 Bxf4 $2 17. Bxh7+ $1 Kxh7 18. Rxf4 Bb7 19. Qg3 {[%csl Rh7][%cal Ga1e1,Ge1e5,Ge5h5] Believe it or not, White is completely winning here. Our pieces are much better than Black's and will swarm the kingside soon enough. A simple and effective plan is [Ra1]-[e1]-[e5]-[h5].} Qd5 {This move looks scary but threatens absolutely nothing. We control [g2] and [f3] so a check on [h1] is useless. Our bishop even defends the rook on [a1].} 20. g5 $18 {Calm yet firm. Some combination of play on the f-, g-, and h-files should suffice.} *

