ng for [d2]-[d4] later.} c5 (10... dxc4 11. bxc4 {⩲ and White has good central control.}) 11. cxd5 Nxd5 (11... exd5 12. f5 $1 {The knight has an unpleasant choice. Either retreat to [e7], when the capture on [f6] will rupture the kingside, or choose the extremely ugly [h8]-square!}) 12. Nc3 Nb4 13. Bb1 $14 {[%cal Gc3e4] White only has a slight advantage, but our position looks so much more fun. The bishops will laser down the board after [Ne4], and we can then consider [Ne4]-[g5] in conjunction with [h2]-[h4]-[h5].} *

