s in trouble and [c6] is also hanging.} Qe8 11. g4 Bg6 12. Qe2 {[%cal Gb1d2,Ge1c1] White will play [Nd2] and [O-O-O], when the h-pawn can be thrown up the board. Black faces enormous issues securing both the [g6]-bishop and the king in view of the incipient pawn storm.} *

