ng control over the [e5]-square.} (8. Be2 {Only 34 games have reached this position and a ton of candidate moves have been essayed. The one with the largest frequency of 22% is} a6 {.}) 8... Ne7 9. c4 {Now [d2]-[d4] and [c4]-[c5] threaten to trap the bishop.} Ng6 10. d4 Be7 11. Ne5 {White has a healthy Stonewall and can look forward to developing with [Bd3] and [Nd2].} Nxe5 12. dxe5 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Ge5f6]} (12. fxe5 Ne4 {would only be slightly better for White.}) 12... Ne4 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gc4d5,Gd1d5]} 13. cxd5 $18 {And Black's center falls!} *

