lowed to exchange on [c6] with an advantage.} 8. Bxc6 $1 Bxc6 (8... bxc6 {needn't even be discussed.} 9. Ne5 {brings White to a great version of previously studied positions in which the bishops on [e7], [d7], and pawn on [a6] are all sub-optimally placed.}) 9. Ne5 Bd7 10. d3 O-O {Trading on [d7] would just redeem us the bishop pair but wouldn't ruin their pawn structure just yet. Instead, we can switch gears and launch a kingside attack. The bishop on [b2] and knight on [e5] are already supremely placed.} 11. Rf3 $1 Be8 12. Rh3 $40 {[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f3,Gf3g5] White will transfer the knight to [g5], when Black's king will get uncomfortable. The heat is certainly being turned up in the kitchen.} *

