at center with} 8. d4 {± . White will castle, play [Nc3], [Rd1], and as soon as possible launch the center further with [e3]-[e4].}) 8. O-O exf4 $2 {This releases the tension too soon.} 9. Qxf4 Ngf6 {Now that Black's e-pawn has left the board prematurely, we are presented with new opportunities.} 10. d4 $16 {[%cal Gc4b3,Ye3e4,Gb1c3] We will play [Bb3] to avoid any ...[Nb6] harassment, [Nc3] and then prepare [e3]-[e4] with a nice advantage from the bishop pair and mobile center.} *

