.[exd5] benefits Black who gets an open e-file for their rook, but this does stop Black from being able to achieve ...[e6]-[e5] easily.} O-O 10. d4 $13 {[%cal Ga2a3,Ge2d3,Yc4c5] Arriving at an interesting Stonewall. We should play [Bd3], [a2]-[a3], and as soon as it is opportune, [c4]-[c5]. Black should aim to break with ...[c6]-[c5] before this, when the game will open up. When this happens, we will have some weaknesses from the Stonewall structure the [e3]-pawn will be weak, but our bishop pair will be strong, keeping the balance.} *

