t a red carpet entrance into the center.} 9. g4 $1 {[%cal Gg4g5] Pushing for [g4]-[g5] to kick the knight out and undermine Black's stability in the center.} Bd6 $2 ({This is not good.} 9... dxc4 10. Bxc4 {transposes back to a position we already reached after 6...dxc4 .}) 10. g5 {Beginning to uncoordinate the black pieces.} Ne4 11. cxd5 cxd5 12. d3 $1 {Pushing the impressive knight out. Black's position falls, as this aggression cannot justify itself.} Nec5 13. Qxd5 $16 {White is up a healthy pawn and Black must play accurately to not let the advantage become decisive immediately.} *

