e4e5] Maintaining control on the dark squares. We should aim to play [e4] shortly and then follow with [e4]-[e5] to crunch on the dark squares or [f4]-[f5] to initiate pawn tension and eventually open Black's kingside. The position is balanced, but it appears that White is in the driver's seat and I would bet most players in this position would choose to take White.} *

