 know from our knowledge of the Key Ideas chapter is not a good version of a Stonewall since Black can respond with an energetic} c5 $1 {⩱ in one punch. White may be able to scrounge equality after some precise moves, but that doesn't mean our opening was a success.}) 6... O-O $1 7. d4 {[%csl Gb4,Gc4,Gd4] Have you ever seen a pawn structure like this? Be honest! Black has a few ways to keep the game level.} Ne4 {This is an interesting way for Black to plan a pawn sacrifice.} 8. Nxe4 dxe4 9. Nd2 f5 {[%cal Gg6g5] Black wants to follow with ...[g5] so we should take care to secure the dark squares.} 10. g3 {[%cal Gf1e2,Gc1a3,Ge1g1] We will follow with [Be2], [Ba3] and [O-O]. White has an interesting position. The game is balanced so getting experience will be paramount.} *

