-knight from [c6] − classic domination! Though, I should mention that Stockfish is convinced that Black has a faint edge after} Bg7 {⩱ .}) 5... Nxd7 $6 {The weaker of Black's options... but the most popular at a frequency of 70%. As it has been mentioned elsewhere, the black knight should go to [c6] in almost every single position in this course. With the knight on [d7], we have no need to worry about the [d4]-square or any potential ...[d5]-[d4] by Black to break up our structure.} 6. O-O Bg7 7. d3 {[%cal Ge3e4] Preparing [e3]-[e4].} Ngf6 $6 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Ge3e4,Ge4e5] We're gonna gradually see why this is an inaccuracy. As our e-pawn makes its way down the board, the [f6]-knight will feel increasingly uncomfortable.} 8. Nc3 $1 {[%csl Rd7,Rd8][%cal Rd5d4,Rd8d4] If only Black's [d7]-knight were anywhere else, then Black could play ...[d5]-[d4] safely and prevent any hopes for [e3]-[e4]...} O-O 9. e4 {Now [e4]-[e5] looms and if Black advances with ...[d5]-[d4], we will reroute to [e2] with a favorable reversed King's Indian.} e6 ({After} 9... d4 10. Ne2 {⩲ , we will play [Qe1], [h2]-[h3] and potentially [g2]-[g4] and [Qe1]-[h4]. White has a nice edge.}) 10. e5 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Ge5f6] The boot we've all been waiting for.} Ne8 {[%csl Rd7,Ge5,Re8,Gf4] Black's knights paint a sorry picture.} 11. Qe2 {[%cal Gc1d2,Gc3d1,Gd1f2] We will play [Bd2] and reroute the [c3]-knight to [f2] to assist with attacking ideas on the kingside. Black is at a loss for what to do. There's nothing to do on the queenside for Black.} f6 {Black has to try something like this.} 12. Nd1 $1 {[%cal Gd1f2,Gf2g4] The knight will wrap around to [g4]. Meanwhile, ...[fxe5] will always be met by [fxe5].} ({After} 12. exf6 Qxf6 {, Black's structure looks ugly, but they will be able to equalize with the thematic ...[e6]-[e5] push soon enough. So this should be avoided.}) 12... fxe5 13. fxe5 Qc7 14. Re1 $16 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gd1f2,Gf2g4] Holding the [e5]-pawn in place. Our knight will continue on its journey to [g4] and we can count on great play on the many weakened dark squares in Black's position.} *

