d2e4] Unless Black goes for the sacrifice this instant, we will play [e4]-[e5] and then [Nd2]-[e4].} Qb6 {[%cal Gc5c4] Aiming for ...[c5]-[c4] with a discovered check. We do not want to allow Black to trade the c-pawns. First, they are ugly and weak. Second, they block Black's bishops tremendously. If they can move the [c5]-pawn and trade it, they will be able to play ...[c6]-[c5] and eventually put the light-squared bishop in a good posturing on [b7].} 11. c4 $1 {[%csl Rc5,Rc6][%cal Ge4e5,Gd2e4] Keeping the pawns fixed. This weakens the dark squares somewhat but no matter, we will play [e4]-[e5] to cement the closed diagonal against the [g7]-bishop.} *

