5 12. b3 $2 {, which would make some great concrete if not for our knight being left hanging on [c3] after} b5 {.}) 11... O-O 12. Bg5 $13 {[%cal Ga1c1,Gd1d3] We will play [Rc1] and [Qd3] with a nice position. Once our queen comes to [d3] we could entertain hopes of building a battery with [Bc2] but of course, we would have to watch out for ...[Nb4].} (12. Bg5 {The position is complex and while objectively balanced, Black has a lot more ways to misstep than White. If Black plays} exf5 {for instance, we can respond with} 13. Bxf6 {and [Nd5] with enormous pressure on [c7], [b6] and [f6].}) *

