hile the iron is hot. Black has not addressed our latent threat of [e4]-[e5] and will be punished for it.} 11. Bxc6 {Chop chop!} bxc6 12. e5 Ng4 13. b3 $18 {[%csl Gb3,Gc4,Rc5,Rc8,Gd3,Re7][%cal Gc1a3,Gc3e4] Black's minor pieces are awful. As is the case for most Rossolimo-style positions, Black's [c8]-bishop has a depressing future ahead of it, and this means we are positionally on top. A simple plan would be to corner the [c5]-pawn with [Qe2] to stop ...[Ng4]-[e3] ideas and then [Ba3] and [Na4] or [Ne4].} *

