her the queen or bishop will drop.}) 12. Qe3 {[%cal Ge3e5,Gb2e5,Gg2g4] Now [g2]-[g4] threatens to win the knight on [h5] so Black must immediately make some big concession.} (12. g4 $4 {would miss the mark.} dxe5 13. gxh5 e4 {and the [b2]-bishop drops along with the mango on [a1].}) 12... f5 13. exd6 Qxd6 14. Bxg7 Nxg7 15. Na3 $16 {[%cal Ga3c4] Aiming for [Nc4] next. By pushing ...[f5], Black has irreparably compromised the e-file, weakening the squares [e5] and [e6]. The [e7]-pawn is also weak. White has an enormous positional advantage.} *

