appens, [axb5] followed by [Ra1]-[a6] might drill our rook into a nice outpost on [a6], when Black’s pawns on [a7], [b5], and [c5] are all vulnerable. White has a slight edge.}) 12. Bxg7 Kxg7 13. e4 {[%csl Rc5,Rg7][%cal Gf3c3] Kicking the knight out while laterally revealing a threat of [Qc3]+.} Nb6 14. Qc3+ Qd4+ 15. Qxd4+ cxd4 16. d3 {[%csl Rb6,Rd4][%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f3] Black's knight on [b6] is bad. We will continue with [Nd2] and play for either [Nd2]-[f3xd4] or [Nd2]-[c4] if Black frees that square by moving the b-pawn.} *

