5,Rd5][%cal Gc3d5,Gc3b5] Initiating an attack against [d5] but also introducing ideas of [Nb5].} e6 {Black reinforces [d5] so we must bring a new piece in to pressure that pawn.} 9. Qf3 {Black must budge now, as other moves to maintain [d5] give us a nice edge.} dxc4 $1 {The pawn capture keeps Black in the game.} 10. Nb5 Qb6 11. a4 {[%cal Ge5c4] Nxc4 is a legitimate issue and Black should develop ASAP even at the cost of worsening the structure.} Nc6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Na3 $14 {[%cal Ga3c4] We will regain the [c4]-pawn with a healthy structure. The computer insists things are only slightly better for White, I assume due to the weak squares on [b3] and [d3], but White's play against the weak c-pawns is obviously more fun. We will snatch [c4], castle, and then play for [d2]-[d3] and [e3]-[e4].} *

