[g3] and possibly [Rf1]-[f2]-[e2].}) 13. Nxd4 cxd4 14. Ne2 {[%csl Rd4] Immediately placing [d4] under uncomfortable pressure.} e5 {This protects [d4] but cedes important control of the light squares.} 15. b4 $1 {[%cal Ge2g3,Gg3f5,Ga4a5] White has an enormous advantage on both sides of the board. We will improve the knight to [g3] (and maybe if allowed to [f5]) , advance the pawn to [a5] to secure the queenside, and gradually raise the pressure.} *

