me questions. If Black succeeds in trading off our c-pawn for their d-pawn, then we'll just have a weak isolated d-pawn... an isolani on [d2]!} 14. Nxd3 {Winning a pawn but fundamentally uncoordinating our pieces.} Qb6+ 15. Nf2 {[%cal Ge2b5] White's extra pawn is fully compensated by the lack of coordination and potentially weak pawns on Black's open c- and d-files. The game is balanced and fun!} *

