{Welcome to the Sidelines of the course! Here we will look at everything that is not part of the ...[d5] systems or the Sicilian family. These include the From's Gambit, Queen's Indian setups, and the Kingside Fianchetto schemes. While these are less common than ...[d5] systems, they still happen relatively frequently and are worthy of our study. I'd recommend paying particular attention to the lines in the From's Gambit. If we forget the theory there, we can end up in serious trouble. However, if we remember our theory and are able to play it correctly, we can count on a definite advantage.} 1. Z0 *

