ke most other variations, the mate threats are counterproductive to Black's entire operation if we can just react calmly.} (11... Bh4 $4 {is a dubious trick. If White captures, Black will retake with the queen and soon win [h1] and then [d1].} 12. Kf2 $1 {The king is alright! White defends the threat and can begin occupying the center with pawns on [d4] and [e4].}) 12. e3 Qh8 {[%cal Gh8h2] The queen navigates the whole board, looking for a way in.} 13. Bg2 Qh2 14. Kf2 $18 {[%cal Gf2g3,Gd1h1] The queen's voyage ends and White can trade the queens off with [Qh1] whenever we want to enter a winning endgame.} *

