22. Qc4 Qe8 23. Rd4 {and here Black can play ...[Qc6] due to the rook on [h8] defending the [d8]-rook.} Qc6 {⇆ , White is not losing but the game is equal and obviously chaotic.}) 17... Rh5 18. Bf4 Bxf4 19. Rxf4 O-O-O 20. Qa6+ Kb8 21. Rc1 {[%cal Gc3c4,Gc1c3,Gc3b3] Threatening [c4] and [Rc3]-[b3].} c5 22. dxc5 Bb7 23. Qc4 Qe8 {[%cal Ge8c6]} 24. Rd4 $1 {[%csl Rd8][%cal Gd4d8]} Rh8 {Black is a move too slow here and White can shut the light-squared bishop out for good} 25. Rxd8+ Qxd8 26. c6 $18 {[%csl Rb7,Gc6] There will be no painful battery with the black queen and bishop on the long diagonal.} *

