 {[%cal Rd1f3,Gf7f5] Preparing to meet [Qf3] with ...[f5].} 13. Nb5 $14 {[%csl Gb5,Rd3,Re4,Ge5][%cal Gb5c3,Gc3e4] Our knights paint a pretty picture. They cover a huge swath of squares in the opponent's camp, keeping Black on their toes. [Nb5]-[c3] is a nice way of trading Black's only good piece on [e4] off the board. White is significantly better. The [d3]-pawn is a permanent target and even in king + pawn endgames might cause Black a decisive disadvantage.} *

