e move to get things going on the kingside.} (7... Nbd7 $2 {is chosen 24% of the time but allows a strong pin on [b5].} 8. Bb5 Bd6 9. Nc6 $1 {⩲ , digging into the weak [c6]-square. Black has an uncomfortable choice: move the queen to the remote [c8]-square, or cede the bishop with ...[Bxc6], when White will dominate the weakened light squares remaining from the expired fianchetto.}) 8. g4 $5 {It's obvious things are headed toward a mess. The g-pawn will go to [g5] if allowed to dig the knight out of [f6]. The position is complex and balanced. This position has only been reached 3 times across all eternity so this offers excellent chances of getting your opponent out of their comfort zone. Each of the 3 games has followed different paths from here − we will address each of the moves tried.} Ne4 9. Nxe4 dxe4 10. g5 {[%cal Gc1e3,Gd1d2,Ge1c1] Here [g5] keeps the enemy queen away from pesky checks on [h4]. We will play [Be3], [Qd2], and castle queenside. The position is set to be chaotic and awesome, enjoy!} *

