um. It's hard to spot, but Black has to castle queenside to cushion the potentially weak d-pawn.} 9. O-O-O Qe7 10. Qe1 {[%cal Gf1b5] Clearing the path for the bishop on [f1].} O-O-O 11. b3 $14 {[%cal Gc1b2] White will play [Kb2] with a solid edge. Black's structure might look better, but we have the bishop pair. A good idea is to try to 'stretch' the board for our bishops by pushing either rook pawn. This will lead to some open diagonals and more importantly, a longer-range fight that our long-range snipers can prosper in.} *

