[%csl Gc4,Gd5,Ge4,Gf4] More space, please. Black is hard-pressed to do anything now.} a6 {[%cal Gb7b5] Trying to strum up some play with ...[b7]-[b5].} 9. a4 $16 {[%cal Ge1g1,Ye4e5,Gh2h3] Clamping down on any resistance. Black's position is miserable due to the lack of space. The minor pieces all bump into each other and don't even get me started on the rooks! We should castle kingside, play [h2]-[h3], and prepare an eventual [e4]-[e5]. Black is already close to lost here as they have 0 counterplay. The [a4] move quelled any possible break on [b5] and so Black is stuck twiddling their thumbs as we make our position better and better in preparation for the eventual central break. An important guideline is to not trade pieces loosely here. Black's pieces lack squares, which is why they are all stuck. If Black could magically trade the knights for ours, for instance, their bishops would immediately gain massively in scope and be significantly improved. So the more black pieces on the board, the more they all suffer!} *

