l Rf6,Rg5][%cal Ge4f6,Ge4g5] White's knight will enter [f6] or [g5] with decisive effect. Note that because White has kept the king's bishop on the board check out [g2], the black pieces fail to cause the white king immediate problems.} Qc1 (20... Rf5 21. Ng5 Rxg5 22. Bf6 $1 {Mate is unavoidable.} Kf7 23. Qg7+ Ke8 24. Bxc6+ $1 {The queen will come to [e7] to end things shortly.}) 21. Ng5 {[%csl Rh7][%cal Gh6h7] Black has to sacrifice the queen to avoid mate on [h7].} *

