1. f4 d5 2. e3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Qd6 4. Nf3 Bg4 {A position that Raven looks at in detail.} 5. b3 ({This is a normal and decent move, but c4 is even more critical.} 5. c4 $1 {is the theoretical move, when things can quickly favor White. For example,} dxc4 6. Na3 e6 7. Nxc4 Qd5 8. Qa4 Bxf3 9. gxf3 Qxf3 10. Rf1 Qd5 11. Ne5 {.}) 5... Nh6 $6 ({For some reason, numerous opponents love putting their knight on this weird square!} 5... Nf6 {is more natural and better.}) 6. Bb2 f6 {[%cal Ge7e5] Black wants ...[e5] and the World, but I am not going to make that happen!} 7. O-O O-O-O 8. c4 $1 {Raven's standard queenside push. This starts opening lines against Black's king.} Nf5 $6 (8... Nb4 $5 {was better:} 9. cxd5 Qxd5 10. Bc4 {.}) 9. Nc3 dxc4 10. bxc4 $14 Bxf3 11. Qxf3 Qxd2 $2 {Greed rarely pays...} 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Qxc6 $18 Rd6 (13... Qxb2 14. Rab1 Qxc3 15. Qe6+ $1 Rd7 16. Qa6+ Kd8 17. Rb8# {is a bit of an issue for Black.}) 14. Qa8+ Kd7 15. Ne4 Qxe3+ (15... Qxb2 16. Nc5#) 16. Kh1 Qb6 17. Ba3 Rc6 18. Rad1+ Nd6 19. c5 Qa5 20. cxd6 1-0

